tasks.content: Download data (1) in ZIP format and leave it as is, do not modify anything.
Select 'New Item' (2) to add data to ArcGIS Online.
Select the 'Your Device' (3) option to add files, or you can drag and drop them from a ZIP folder or 'Drag and drop your file or choose an option' area.
Find the downloaded folder named 'Les3Valees_Geodatabase_files_stay_in_zip_EN' if you haven't changed its name, and locate it.
Next, expand the list (5) and select the 'File Geodatabase' option (6).
Then leave the default option (8) click 'Next' (9).
In the last step, you can change the name (10), create a folder (11), and click 'Save' (12).
This way, you have created your resources in the ArcGIS Online environment (13), and you can find in the 'Content' tab.
